txt.en: 'Something's not right here....'
'Someone is about in the halls, but they won't make it far!'
'These halls belong to the Frost-horde!'
'Keep your eyes open, worms. There's someone here!'
Thikil-gundu
'Fine! I'll kill 'em myself if you lot can't manage it!'
'What do we have here?'
'You... should not be here....'
<rgb=#FF0000>'Fine! I'll kill 'em myself if you lot can't manage it!'</rgb>
'Thikil-gundu... is... ours!'
'Ah! Not quite dead after all, are ya? Karkasht will fix that!'
'Do not let them pass, maggots! The dragons must be protected!'
'I have seen enough!'
'Is that what you had hoped for? An end to your pursuit?'
Karazgar, the Weeping Warrior
'No... it is merely the beginning! Hrímil shall soon be mine, and the world will be shaped anew!'
You must have completed 'Discovery: Thikil-gundu, the Steel Keep' to play this instance.
'To me, Vethúg! The Anvil awaits....'
'All right, you bearded icicles! Here I come!'
'How did you get in here? What have you done to her?!
'At last you have come....'
'You have sought for dragons and dwarves, but at what cost?'
<rgb=#FF0000>'What's goin' on out there, maggots? You lot better not have stoked the fires again!'</rgb>
'It is time your mettle was tested!'
<rgb=#FF0000>'You know the rules! Throw 'em into the pits or it's all of your heads!'</rgb>
<rgb=#FF0000>'If the dead ones get in again, I'll have Athramóth show you just how cold you worms can be!'</rgb>
'It... burns....'
'Too... hot....'
'Enough of these distractions! Now your true test begins!'
'You think... that... will stop me?'
'Aghhhh....'
'If the dwarves get in, we cut 'em down. Same as always!'
'Your power... is mine!'
'Which one of you lot opened that door? It won't be on my head when the dwarves get loose again!'
'All of your kind will serve me!'
'I do what Athramóth tells me... and you do what I tell you!'
<rgb=#FF0000>'And you call yourselves Orcs! Are a couple of bearded icicles too much for you?'</rgb>
'Grant me the strength of your brood!'
'One of you lot best get out there and seal the doors!'
